questions.explanation:
**1. Minimize and Compress:**

# Minify CSS
cssnano input.css output.css

# Gzip compression (server-side)
gzip -c styles.css > styles.css.gz

**2. Critical CSS:**

<!-- Inline critical CSS -->
<style>
.header {
background: #333;
}
.hero {
padding: 2rem;
}
</style>

<!-- Load non-critical CSS asynchronously -->
<link
rel="preload"
href="styles.css"
as="style"
onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'"
/>

**3. Efficient Selectors:**

/* Good - specific and fast */
.header .nav-item {
}

/* Bad - too generic */
* {
}

/* Bad - complex descendant */
div div div div div {
}

**4. Use CSS Containment:**

.component {
contain: layout style paint;
}

**5. Avoid Expensive Properties:**

/* Expensive - causes reflow */
.element {
width: 100px;
height: 100px;
}

/* Better - uses transform */
.element {
transform: scale(1.1);
}

**6. CSS-in-JS Optimization:**

// Use CSS-in-JS libraries that extract CSS
import styled from 'styled-components';

const Button = styled.button`
background: ${props => (props.primary ? 'blue' : 'gray')};
`;

**1. CSS Custom Properties (Variables):**

:root {
--primary: #3498db;
--spacing: 1rem;
}

.element {
color: var(--primary);
margin: var(--spacing);
}

**2. CSS Grid:**

.grid {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
gap: 2rem;
}

**3. CSS Flexbox:**

.flex {
display: flex;
justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
}

**4. CSS Container Queries:**

.card {
container-type: inline-size;
}

@container (min-width: 300px) {
.card__content {
display: flex;
}
}

**5. CSS Logical Properties:**

.element {
margin-inline-start: 1rem; /* left in LTR, right in RTL */
margin-block-end: 2rem; /* bottom */
}

**6. CSS Subgrid:**

.grid {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: subgrid;
}

**7. CSS Cascade Layers:**

@layer base, components, utilities;

@layer base {
body {
margin: 0;
}
}

@layer components {
.button {
padding: 1rem;
}
}
